Me and AC-130 have officially ended our first season hunting together. We took a total of 21 head of game: 11 marsh rabbits and 10 grey squirrels. She is an excellent hunter and I’m excited for at least one more season together. 
.
I ended earlier than most but my GPS is broken, my February is slammed busy and I’m happy with the season we had. Hopefully she starts molting soon and we can get back out there in September/October. 
.
Over the next several months while I take a break from falconry I’ll be focusing on my fitness again, building and maintaining our chicken coop and getting my budget organized. Fingers crossed for a new 4Runner for the next falconry season, I miss my old one 🫠
.

It’s molting season! My Red-tailed Hawk has lost 6 of her juvenile tail feathers so far, and is growing a couple new adult feathers in. This is one of my favorite things about flying Red-tailed Hawks. It’s like unwrapping a Christmas present for 4 months, watching them develop their adult plumage. She was a gorgeous juvie, and she’s gonna be a gorgeous adult! I’ll probably fly her for at least one more season, maybe even keep her for one more after that depending.
